<!--
  PROFILE CUSTOM CONTENT SNIPPET

  Adds the Inklings tab content to the character profile page.

  FILE: ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs

  INSTALLATION:

  1. Open your game's ares-webportal/app/components/profile-custom.hbs
  2. Copy the code block below this comment:
     - If the file is empty or nearly empty, paste it as-is
     - If the file already has other tab-pane divs, add it after the closing </div> of
       another tab-pane entry (maintain the existing indentation and structure)

  IMPORTANT DETAILS:

  ID MATCHING:
  - The id="inklings-tab-pane" MUST match the href in profile-custom-tabs.snippet.hbs
  - Do NOT change this value

  PROPERTY NAMES:
  - These must match the property names used in your profile-custom.hbs
  - If your profile uses "character" instead of "char", update all instances
  - See the rest of your profile-custom.hbs to find the correct names

  REQUIRED BACKEND SETUP:
  - You must also install the get_fields_for_viewing hook from
    custom-install/custom_char_fields.snippet.rb (Step 2) or the type
    dropdown will be empty and staff won't see their permission override.

  WEB PORTAL OPTIONAL:
  - This component is entirely optional - if you're running MUSH-only,
    you do not need this snippet or the related components at all.
-->

<div class="tab-pane fade" id="inklings-tab-pane">
  {{inklings-tab characterId=this.char.id characterName=this.char.name viewerId=this.viewer.id isStaff=this.char.custom.can_manage_inklings isApproved=this.char.is_approved isSelf=(eq this.char.id this.viewer.id) typeInfo=this.char.custom.inkling_types}}
</div>
